@notice Users can buy an equal amount of A and B tokens
@param _numberOfTokens The number of A and B tokens requested
@notice admin can change the contract state to "active"
@notice admin can change the contract state to "triggered"
@notice admin can change the contract state to "timedout"

typeDescriptions.typeString: function (struct Chainlink.Request memory,string memory,string memory) pure
function (struct Chainlink.Request memory,string memory,string memory) pure

buyTokens(uint256).notice: Users can buy an equal amount of A and B tokens

params._numberOfTokens: The number of A and B tokens requested

isOwner().details: Returns true if the caller is the current owner.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

redeem(address,uint256).notice: Allows users to exchange either A or B tokens for ETH

params._numberOfTokens: The number of A or B tokens to be redeemed
params._token: The type of token being redeemed (must be A or B)

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

trigger_active().notice: admin can change the contract state to "active"

trigger_timeout().notice: admin can change the contract state to "timedout"

trigger_triggered().notice: admin can change the contract state to "triggered"
